---
title: Garlicky Chicken with Burrata & Mushroom Ravioli Elevated Dinners, Impressively Easy
description: Tender ravioli are pretty much a win in any form, but they’re especially delish when packed with savory, earthy mushrooms (and when they take just 15 minutes to make!). Toss those ravioli in a delicious cream sauce bright with fresh lemon, then add tender, sweet peas and top with a garlicky perfectly seared chicken cutlet. Shower with burrata (creamy, fresh mozzarella), drizzle with olive oil, and a final sprinkle of lemon zest, and oh—what’s that thumping sound? Ah yes, it’s the beating of our pasta-loving hearts!
